gomodel:SYNGO_4166  a     owl:Ontology ;
        rdfs:comment      "Rationale: Fig 6 shows selective presynaptic labeling of GAP-43 using DAB precipitate as a marker (indicated by the arrows) which can be observed near the plasma membrane and near synaptic vesicles. Panel A-D is rat material, E is cat.\nFig 7 shows ultrastructural colocalization of GAP-43 (by DAB precipitate) and GABA (by conjugated gold) in presynaptic terminals. This colocalization is quantified in table 1.\n\nOn the antibody used: \"A monoclonal antiserum (clone 9-1E12, Chemicon, Temecula, CA, USA; formerly from Boehr- inger Mannheim, and Roche, Indianapolis, IN, USA) was used to identify GAP-43. Characterisation of the antiserum and preab- sorption controls have been carried out by others (Zou et al., 1996) and by the manufacturer.\". Experimental description: M&M: \"..Three adolescent (22-25 days), four adult (85-108 days), and three older adult (1 year) male Long Evans hooded rats were anesthetized with....\"" ;
        lego:modelstate   "production" ;
        dc:contributor    "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-2514-0216" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0001-5259-4945" ;
        dc:date           "2020-12-02" ;
        dc:title          "SYNGO_CC_4166" ;
        pav:providedBy    "https://syngo.vu.nl" ;
        biolink:in_taxon  "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/NCBITaxon_10116" .

